{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b0028d30-c87d-49c2-bb14-5779fe0992cf","content":"`.testsettings` is a legacy format that modern MSTest (v3+) no longer honors. Here's what I did:\n\n**Created `local.runsettings`** — the modern equivalent — mapping each setting:\n\n| `.testsettings` | `.runsettings` |\n|---|---|\n| `<Property name=\"TestTimeout\" value=\"30000\" />` | `<TestSessionTimeout>30000</TestSessionTimeout>` |\n| `<TestDirectory useLoadContext=\"true\" />` | `<MSTest><AssemblyResolution>` block |\n| `<DataCollector>` (CodeCoverage/1.0) | `<DataCollector>` (CodeCoverage/2.0) |\n\n**Updated `.csproj`** to point to the new file via `<RunSettingsFilePath>`.\n\nYou can safely delete `local.testsettings` once you've verified tests run correctly. You can also pass the runsettings at the CLI: `dotnet test --settings local.runsettings`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0313ed2d-181f-447e-ba39-60c6d98bc304","outputTokens":245,"requestId":"0423:C1158:23999C5:282A230:69E830E8"},"id":"6ba1a7b9-7f89-49bb-b270-004098d290a2","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:22:39.784Z","parentId":"8e8428c8-6035-4160-ad0e-6ca2361c57ef"}
